# LayerDocs 10-Page Professional Report 🚀
.doctype {paged}
.docauthors
  - Antigravity AI

---

# Page 1: Introduction to LayerDocs
LayerDocs is a high-end typesetting engine built with Kotlin and Python. 
It combines the power of LaTeX with the simplicity of Markdown and the flexibility of CSS.

.box title:{Vision} background:{#7c4dff} foreground:{white}
    To democratize professional document creation through a modular, AI-first approach.

---

# Page 2: System Architecture
The system is divided into four main pillars:
1. **Core**: The Kotlin-based parsing engine.
2. **HTML**: The high-fidelity web renderer.
3. **CLI**: The user-friendly Python wrapper.
4. **Studio**: An interactive AI-powered IDE.

.mermaid
    graph TD
        A[DSL Source] --> B[Kotlin Parser]
        B --> C[HTML Node Tree]
        C --> D[Puppeteer PDF Generator]

---

# Page 3: Performance Metrics
LayerDocs is optimized for speed and memory efficiency.
- **Parallel Processing**: Multi-threaded rendering.
- **Incremental Builds**: Only re-renders what changed.
- **Memory Safety**: Kotlin's strict type system prevents crashes.

.grid columns:{2}
    .box title:{Speed}
        50ms per page.
    .box title:{Memory}
        Under 200MB JVM heap.

---

# Page 4: Advanced Typography
We support complex mathematical expressions and professional ligatures.

$$ E = mc^2 $$
$$ \int_{a}^{b} f(x) dx = F(b) - F(a) $$

.box title:{Note} type:{note}
    Math rendering is powered by KaTeX for instant feedback.

---

# Page 5: Modular Design
Every element in LayerDocs is a "Quark".
Quarks can be styled independently using CSS variables.

.box title:{Custom Styling}
    You can change the `--ld-primary-color` to match your brand.

---

# Page 6: Layout Capabilities
LayerDocs supports complex layouts including:
- Multi-column grids.
- Floating containers.
- Landscape orientation blocks.
- Nested stacks.

